  "texts": [
    "Indeed, even detecting these technical difficulties is made easier with AI.",
    "For instance, facial recognition software could flag webcam issues, while AI audio detection could flag whether there is no audio feed for a test that might require the student to speak.",
    "Nevertheless, human review of these flags would still be required (Nigam et al., 2021), and ideally, a combination of AI and human live remote proctoring would be employed (Dyer, 2024).",
    "Some of the risks listed above could be mitigated by employing a hybrid remote proctoring model that uses both AI detection and live human proctors.",
    "Alternatively, the needed human review of AI-assigned flags could happen asynchronously, with the recordings being reviewed to determine whether an academic integrity violation occurred."
  ],
